President Donald J. Trump had a conversation with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan. They both expressed their dedication to achieving permanent and verifiable denuclearization of North Korea and pledged to continue coordinating before the talks between the United States and North Korea. They also reiterated the importance of North Korea abandoning all weapons of mass destruction and ballistic missile programs. President Trump also mentioned that he will encourage North Korea to quickly resolve the issue of Japanese citizens who were abducted by North Korea.